# Scenario Documentation Sync

When making changes related to scenario testing in `WarLeague.Test`, always update scenario docs in `WarLeague.Test/Scenarios/`.

## Required updates after scenario-related changes

- Update `PROGRESS.md` with completed items and current next steps.
- Update `ROADMAP.md` checkbox states when roadmap tasks move.
- Update `BACKLOG.md` checkbox states when items are added, promoted, or completed.
- Keep checklist format consistent (`- [ ]` and `- [x]`).
- If architecture/pattern changes (for example test class structure), reflect it in `README.md`.

## Scope trigger

Apply this whenever edits touch:

- `WarLeague.Test/ScenarioSpecifications.cs`
- `WarLeague.Test/ScenarioBuilder.cs`
- any new scenario spec/builder files under `WarLeague.Test`
